## Ingredients

- [ ] 2 cups cottage cheese
- [ ] 1/4 cup cocoa powder
- [ ] 2 tablespoons maple syrup (or powdered sugar)

## Recipe

1. Add the cottage cheese, cocoa powder, and maple syrup to a high-speed blender or food processor. Blend everything together, scraping down the sides, until smooth.
2. Transfer the mousse to serving dishes and serve immediately or chill for at least an hour to thicken.

## Notes

1. Makes 2 servings with 30g protein per serving
2. Suggested serving size: 1 cup (half the recipe)
3. For a smoother texture, blend longer or start with whipped cottage cheese before adding cocoa and syrup
4. Refrigerate up to 3 days or freeze for up to 2 months
5. Can substitute cottage cheese with Greek yogurt for similar results
